title: Castle Rock High School
text:
Castle Rock High School is a <a href="Rural%20area">rural</a> <a href="public%20high%20school">public high school</a> in <a href="Castle%20Rock%2C%20Washington">Castle Rock, Washington</a>.
Academics.
14% of Castle Rock students take an <a href="Advanced%20Placement">Advanced Placement</a> (AP) exam, with 2% having passed the AP exam. 18% of Castle Rock students are proficient in math and 55% are proficient in reading. Castle Rock is well below the state median for proficiency in both graduation rates and proficiency scores.
Castle Rock has a graduation rate of 80%. 
Demographics.
Castle Rock is a predominantly <a href="White%20people">white</a> high school, with 79% of its students considering themselves white. The two other most popular racial/ethinc groups are <a href="Hispanic">Hispanic</a> and <a href="Two%20or%20more%20races">Two or more races</a>.
47% of students are female, and 53% are male. 47% are economically disadvantaged, with 48% forming part of the free or reduced lunch programs. 
Sports.
Castle Rock is a member of the <a href="Washington%20Interscholastic%20Activities%20Association">Washington Interscholastic Activities Association</a> (WIAA) and competes in the Southwest Washington District 4 Trico 1A league. The Trico 1A consists of eight teams.
